<img class="left" src="img/sulfur-bohr.gif" width="100px" />Sulfur is the chemical element that has the <span class="yh">atomic number 16</span>. It is a <span class="yh">widely-found non-metal</span> that has been <span class="yh">known about throughout human history</span>. It can be <span class="yh">found in nature</span> as a pure element as well as in its sulfide and sulfate (mineral) forms. Sulfur is an <span class="yh">essential element in life</span> - it's a minor component of fats, body fluids, and skeletal minerals. It's also used very widely for <span class="yh">man-made purposes</span>; including as a component of fertilizers, gunpowder, matches, insecticides, pesticides, and fungicides.
